Package com.cafean.client.ui.util

Class InsertionSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.ui.util.InsertionSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelElement
    public abstract class InsertionSource
extends java.lang.Object
implements ModelElement
    This class encapsulates the source of a component insertion. It is used by the Toolbox and the Navigator to give components fine grained control of their insertion process. This allows components to cancel their insertion or include other component creation in the process while still maintaining a single undo-able event.
    See Also:
    componentAdded(AbstractComponent, boolean), getEdit(), getModel()

    • Method Detail

      • componentAdded

        public void componentAdded​(AbstractComponent component,
                           boolean primaryComponent)
        Notifies this insertion source that the given component has been added to the model. This method should be called for each component added during the insertion to ensure that the UI is updated to accommodate the newly inserted components.

        This method does NOT add the component to the model. The component must be added to the model directly using AbstractComponent.addToModel(AbstractModel, boolean).

        Note that this method does NOT create an UndoableInsert for the given component. Undo-able edits must be added directly to the included edit.

        Parameters:
        component - the AbstractComponent that was just added to the model
        primaryComponent - true if this component is the primary focus of the insertion; false if it was created as a consequence of the insertion

      • finish

        public void finish()
        Notifies this insertion source that the insertion is finished and it should perform any final processing required. This final processing includes ending and posting the edit and setting the model dirty.

      • getEdit

        public final javax.swing.undo.CompoundEdit getEdit()
        Returns the edit that should be used for the insertion. Note that this edit begins the process empty. To support undo/redo component insertions must include at least an UndoableInsert object.
        Returns:
        the CompoundEdit that should be used for the insertion.

      • addUndoableInsert

        public final void addUndoableInsert​(AbstractComponent component)
        Adds an UndoableInsert object to this source's CompoundEdit. This convenience method is provided to avoid a compile-time dependency on UndoableInsert to each component.
        Parameters:
        component - the AbstractComponent for which to add an UndoableInsert.
